Text.Value: What do you want?
Wait, no! Come back! I haven't blessed you yet!
Felt a bit lowbrow for Naaber. What's a bard going to do, sing at you? Hah!
Look! A displacer beast! Go after it!
Wooooooow. That was awesome! I bet it even works when you do it.
Yay! You spoke to me! Nobody ever talks to me.
So what do you say - did I scare ya?
But... you're the one who keeps talking to me.
Maybe pick a different career.
Let me focus... I can feel the power deep within me... it's coming up! It's coming up!
Wait, wait! I promise I won't turn you into a flumph! I literally don't know how!
Oh wow, yours is much better.
Why do so many professions have to be done in silence?!
*As he empties himself of his latest slew of thoughts, you take the opportunity to slip away.*
No, you're not. I see you. You're right there.
But we can still be friends, right? Right?
Wait wait. What if I mix the classes... Oh Naaber, you GENIUS!
What in the hells are you doing now?
Are you trying to... pray?
Wait, there's another step after that? Rats.
Leave.
You were great! Keep at it!
Was someone talking? I hear them, but I can't see them!
Oh pish! I'm great at being your friend. And that's all that matters! Friendship! Yay!
Really? But... I'm ready to do anything.
Oh thank goodness. I was worried I was getting too good at it and nobody would ever see me again.
What is it this time? Bard?
My patron might still be in the market for souls. I'll put in a good word for you.
Let me guess, you've decided to try being a barbarian?
*Puuurr!*
That wasn't it, was it? Bum.
Oh... sorry - shit. I didn't know bards had to bake too...
*Naaber seals his lips, but you feel the pressure of words behind them. The poor thing is straining fit to burst.*
It's pronounced 'grovel afore me or die'.
Leave.
Oh HI! I didn't see you there! I was deep in meditation, see.
*Woof woof!* I'm a dog!
Right you are! I'll just... find something to punch... I guess...
Sure. Why not.
I've decided to be a monk!
Here's a tip from a real fighter - less talking, more fighting.
Here's a tip to get you started - less talking, more fighting.
Duuuuuh.
You're very kind, but I can tell that you're humouring me. Everyone's always humouring me. *Sigh.*
Wait, don't leave me hanging!
It's a good job I ran into you!
I am a bit too chatty, aren't I? Haha. OH WELL.
What do you think? Am I a good bard?
Happy birthday to you, happy birthday to you, happy biiiiiiirthday dear...
Ummmmmmmmmm...
Did I just break something? I hope it wasn't anything important. Ha... ha...
That's right! You got it! Oh yay!
Say nothing.
As soon as I figure out what kind of adventurer I'm going to be... What do you think? Could I be a fighter?
It isn't? Shoot. What did you think, anyway?
Does your magic come from the thrumming scream of chaos itself?
Do you draw your magic from draconic ancestry like me?
Does your magic also come from the beating heart of the storm?
I liked you more as a human.
Haha! Why would I do that?
I'm pretending to be a dog. Everyone likes dogs!
You're great at nothing. In fact, you're the worst person I've ever met.
You don't know when to shut up, do you?
Here's a pact for you. Give up.
Everyone likes dogs!
My only command is that you never speak to me again.
Perhaps the answer was deep within me all along... an ancient spark of arcana... Yes, I was born to be a sorcerer, I can feel it.
Are you ready for the long, drawn-out silences of an assassin's pursuit?
Never sing again.
*Burp.* Oops. Just indigestion. Haha.
Stop it. Just stop it.
I don't accept.
BOOOOOOOOOO.
What idiot? Where? Where?
Yaaaaay! Friends! This is the best day of Naaber's life.
Follow your dreams and find out.
Isn't peace and quiet just the best?
ROAAAAAARRRRR!
Ommmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmm...
Happy biiiiiirthdaaaaay toooooooo yoooooooou!!!
I'm going to be the best monk there ever was!
I'm praying. Is that not how it goes?
I take it you've decided to try being a monk?
Shut up shut up shut up.
Could I be a good bard?
Oh you didn't get it.
Then you must follow my commands. My first is this - break your oath. Now.
Leave him to it.
My bladder control is exemplary, I'm afraid.
Are you sure you're ready to be a warlock? To sell your soul for eternity?
What are you talking about? I can shut up whenever I want!

Aaaaaaargh! Ican'tdoitIhavetoomuchtosay! You were right. I can't be a monk. I just want to TALK. Talking's great, see? You can say words, make friends, tell everyone everything you're thinking and feeling...
Yep! That's right! Help me out here. Happy biiiiiirthday deeeeear...
Guess old Naaber's more of a talker than a fighter.
...School? School?
Wizard. W - I - Z - A - R - D. Wizard.
That's spelling. Wizards cast spells. Idiot.
I hope you're looking forward to those long, lonely months on the trail.
I can swear a different oath if you like? Come baaaaaack!
My piss lies dormant, but my gorge rises.
What happened to being a bard? I thought you were enjoying that?
Correct. But nobody likes Naaber.
Join in.
I - I don't want to - all right. An oath's an oath, I suppose...
Put what up?
What if no one ever talks to me again?! NOOOOOOOO!
I doubt you'll find peace, but the rest of us might. If we're lucky.
Brace for a fight.
Oh. Shit.
Godsdammit, why are so many adventurer jobs so lonely?! I thought you were supposed to have parties?
*Bark! Bark!*
My liege. I swear to you an undying oath of absolute devotion. I am but your humble paladin.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Use HUM_M_Rig_DFLT_CINE_Bows_Kneel_01 to show Naaber kneeling.

Text.Value: I am afraid I am sworn to an oath of my own. I cannot be your master.
Uh... no.
You? The apex predator? No.
My soul? I have to give up my soul to become a warlock?
Oh. Oh. Oh no... Something inside me feels very wrong...
There's learning involved? Noooooooooo.
Bless us with your gentle - no, holy - spirit - no, soul - no, spirit... your powers - your divine powers... bother.
Wait! I wasn't really going to fight you! I was just trying something out!
Pretend to be terrified.
Wait! Wait! You didn't answer!
I regret ever talking to you.
If not a rogue, then a ranger. I'm great at chasing things down.
Why don't you actually fight me and I'll tell you?
My name's Naaber, adventurer-to-be, soon to be the best adventurer anyone's ever seen.
Leave.
Awwww, that's so nice of you to say! Thanks! I hope so too! Bet it's really warm there.
Sing your name in a long, high, operatic tone.
Oh well. BACK TO THE NAABING BOARD.
Back quietly away.
Put 'em up put 'em up!
Oh - you meant me. Haha, good one!
But why? We're having so much fun!
What are you sniffing?
Oof. Is that what good sounds like? Gross.
Wooooooow. That was so much better than I'll ever be.
Hello! Hi!
Show me what you can do.
You're very good at this! Perhaps you can teach me. I'm trying to pray.
Phew. I was hoping you'd say that. To tell you the truth, I don't actually like hurting people very much. Or getting hurt.
Thank you!
I know this one. You're a wizard.
Whatever you're doing, I'm pretty sure you're doing it wrong.
No no, it's definitely something...
Sure. I guess.
No, I've decided I'm going to be a cleric. Now if you'll excuse me, I must pray.
Are we still not done yet?
How wondrous. What school of magic is your specialty?
I'M SORRY I CAN'T DO IT I'M JUST TOO EXCITED TO TALK TO YOU.
Oh well. Back to the Naabing board!
Am I doing it right?
You... liked me?! Happy day!
What are you doing?
Walk away.
Know any fiendish philanthropists? Fickle fae financiers? Eldritch employers? I want to make a pact.
Ah ha! You fell for it!
What? Where?
Leave.
You're humouring me again, aren't you? Oh well... back to the Naabing board.
I was sculpted from a slice of Bhaal's own dead flesh. I have no birthday.
Come on - play along now. Haaaaaappy biiiiiirthday deeeear...
Oooooh I might be too good at this. What if no one ever sees me again?!
Haha! You're funny!
Leave.
Ammmmmmmmmmmm...
Urgh. It's no use. I can't do it.
But I - How am I supposed to -
I really like talking to you. There's not a lot of people that want to talk to me so I bought you a present. Here.
Now what are we going to talk about if not about the adventuring life?
It won't hurt, will it? No, surely not...
It's more like... By your sacrament ever be praised. Oh holy, most wise, eternal god...
What's your favourite spell?
Er... sure.
Come back, friend!
Sure...
Nope!
Go back to being silent, then.
Cool, can you do any magic?
ROAR! *Cough cough cough.*

EditorData.NodeContext: Roar descends into feeble spluttering and coughing.

Text.Value: Leave.
Wait a minute... you were pulling my leg! Haha! Good one! But you're not getting rid of old Naaber that easily.
So how did I do? Are you quaking in your boots with fear?
Wait! I didn't mean to scare you off! Come back!
Um - sure. I'll just... raise my fists and...
I have done many terrible things, but I regret none more than listening to you.
Leave.
It's not my birthday.
Leave.
Please just go away.
Leave.
What you're feeling is delusion.
I think you're not even worth being sacrificed to Lord Bhaal.
Sidle away from him slowly.
Appreciate the honesty. *Sigh.*
I could not give less of a shit.
Finally, some peace and quiet.
No, spell. As in magic spell. The thing wizards cast.
What god are you praying to?
And mean.
Where's my birthday cake?
I'd cut out your tongue, but I want to know you've inflicted this misery on the rest of the city.
Oh. I don't have one of those. Balls. Back to the Naabing board, then...
*Sniff sniff.*
There's more than one?! Shit.
Sniff him back.
All the bards I've met play an instrument.
An admirable pursuit. Those creatures understand the true meaning of life.
Our holy - um - most holy - sacrilege - heretic? GOD. Bless us. Please?
That's not true! My mum does. Wait no, she loves me, but does she actually like me...?

EditorData.NodeContext: trails off into his own thoughts

Text.Value: No pact needed. I hope a devil finds you and takes you straight to the Hells.
Please don't leave! I don't want to be alone.
Ha ha ha! Very good! And you're a pain in the arm!
Oh wow, that sounds awful. I don't think I want to sound like that.
Oh. All right, then! Sorry to bother you!
Not even slightly.
Maybe not... *Cough.*
I LIKE TALKING. TALKING IS THE BEST.
*A faint, muffled squeak accompanies your departure - Naaber, trying to stop himself from giving away his position.*
Oh yeah? Prove it.
Wow. You're really mean.
Ooooohhhhhh! Whoopsie!
BOO! Bet you didn't even see me coming. I'm a shadow, a master of sneakery. A rogue.
You're joking, right? Because that's what friends do?
Wait, come back! I was only pretending!
Carry on, then.
Are you scared? Did you wet your pants? Did you? Did you?
Behold, mundane meddler. You step in the domain of a master speller. For I am to be a most mighty WIZARD.
Why do I keep talking to this idiot? Why? Why?
That's not a pact. That's just an order... Oh-ho! Very good! You nearly had me there!
You? You can't shut up.
Am I boring you? I feel like I'm boring you.
Boo? Where?
Oh. Oh. That hurts, you know?
Leave.
STOP IT, YOU IDIOT.
These roles sure are restrictive, aren't they? Maybe the adventuring life's just not for me.
Your fists, silly! I'm trying something out.
Waaaaaait! You're going too fast!
Bhaal said I would go mad... is it happening already? Is this idiot my tormenter?
Roar! Roar! ROAAAR!
You are a pain in the arse, that's what you are.
YES! Naaber has found his calling!

Synopsis: Naaber's dialog at Carmen's Cosmetics Shop in Wyrm's Crossing. He's very annoying and going through his entire dialog will give you an experience reward.
